## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

**Critical: 1 systemic issue (affects 10/10 tests) · High: 0 · Medium: 1 · Low: 1**

This is a textbook **coverage-touching** test class. Every public method on `ProductCatalog` is called (achieving high line coverage), but almost nothing is actually verified. These tests will pass even if the production code is completely broken — they only prove the methods don't throw.

---

### 🔴 Critical — Coverage Touching / Missing Assertions

**Pattern:** Systematic invocation of every public method with zero or trivial (`IsNotNull`) assertions. 6 of 10 tests have **no assertion at all**. The remaining 4 use only `Assert.IsNotNull`, which verifies the method returned *something* — never that the result is *correct*.

| Test Method | Line | Issue |
|---|---|---|
| `AddProduct_Works` | 17 | No assertion — never verifies product was stored |
| `UpdatePrice_Works` | 32 | No assertion — never verifies price changed to 14.99 |
| `RemoveProduct_Works` | 38 | No assertion — never verifies product is gone |
| `GetProductCount_Works` | 63 | No assertion — doesn't even check the count |
| `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` | 68 | No assertion — never verifies discounted prices |
| `ImportFromCsv_Works` | 85 | No assertion — never verifies product was imported |
| `GetProduct_Works` | 24 | `IsNotNull` only — doesn't verify SKU, Name, or Price |
| `SearchProducts_Works` | 46 | `IsNotNull` only — doesn't verify count or content |
| `GetAllProducts_Works` | 55 | `IsNotNull` only — doesn't verify count or content |
| `ExportToCsv_Works` | 77 | `IsNotNull` only — doesn't verify CSV content |

**Why this is dangerous:** A bug in `UpdatePrice` (e.g., saving the old price) would never be caught. A bug in `ApplyBulkDiscount` (e.g., wrong math) passes silently. You get 95% coverage and zero confidence.

**Concrete fixes:**

```csharp
// BEFORE — AddProduct_Works (line 17)
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_Works()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);
}

// AFTER
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_ProductIsRetrievableBysku()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);

    var stored = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual("Widget", stored?.Name);
    Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, stored?.Price);
}
```

```csharp
// BEFORE — UpdatePrice_Works (line 32)
_catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);

